    <section>
      <h2>What an app can and cannot fix</h2>
      <p>
        An app can absolutely make your brewing more consistent. It can keep your timing honest, remind you of ratios, save the recipe that finally worked, and stop you from re-learning the same lesson every other week. That is real value.
      </p>
      <p>
        But an app cannot fix stale beans, a sloppy grind, or a brewer full of old oils. If your coffee tastes dull, bitter, or weirdly flat no matter what the phone says, the problem may be somewhere else in the chain. That is why I think app advice works best when paired with a grinder you trust and a scale that stops the guessing.
      </p>
      <p>
        Put another way: the app is the coach, not the athlete. Helpful coach, yes. Miracle worker, no.
      </p>
    </section>

